<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <!--
    Exceptions to the hardened runtime (which package.sh enables at signing time).
    Tscribe intentionally needs NONE:

      * Not sandboxed, so it keeps full read access to user-selected media anywhere
        on disk (no app-sandbox / file-access keys).
      * It spawns its bundled CLIs (whisper-cli, sherpa diarizer) as separate,
        independently-signed processes. That is not code injection, so no allow-*
        injection exceptions are needed.
      * Neither the app nor the CLIs JIT or map unsigned executable memory.
      * Outgoing network (the Standard edition model download) is unaffected by the
        hardened runtime; that is a sandbox concern, and we are not sandboxed.

    If notarization ever reports a library-validation failure for a bundled binary,
    add the key com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation set to true, and
    note it usually belongs on that CLI's own signing rather than on the app.

    Keep this file free of double-hyphens: AMFI's XML parser rejects them inside
    comments (they are illegal in XML), and plutil will NOT catch it.
  -->
</dict>
</plist>
